# usePrevious Hook

Sometimes you need to know the previous value of a state or prop. You can store it in a ref.

```jsx
function usePrevious(value) {
  const ref = useRef();
  useEffect(() => {
    ref.current = value;
  }, [value]);
  return ref.current;
}
```

Usage:
```jsx
function Counter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  const prevCount = usePrevious(count);
  return <p>Now: {count}, before: {prevCount}</p>;
}
```

